Interface Extender

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    KSI

    public interface Extender
extends Closeable
    An instance of this class can be obtained using ExtenderBuilder class.

    • Method Detail

      • extend

        KSISignature extend(KSISignature signature)
             throws KSIException
        Extends signature to the "closest" publication in publication file.
        Parameters:
        signature - signature to be extended. not null.
        Returns:
        KSISignature extended keyless signature
        Throws:
        KSIException - when error occurs (e.g when communication with KSI service fails)

      • extend

        KSISignature extend(KSISignature signature,
                    PublicationRecord publicationRecord)
             throws KSIException
        Extends the signature to specified publication record. The publication time of the publication record must be after signature aggregation time. When signature is extended then the old calendar hash chain and publication record is removed.
        Parameters:
        signature - signature to be extended. not null.
        publicationRecord - publication record to extend. not null.
        Returns:
        extended keyless signature with extended calendar hash chain and publication record
        Throws:
        KSIException - when error occurs (e.g when communication with KSI service fails)

      • asyncExtend

        Future<KSISignature> asyncExtend(KSISignature signature)
                          throws KSIException
        This method is used to extend signature asynchronously to closest publication. Use method Future.getResult() to get the extended keyless signature.
        Parameters:
        signature - instance of KSISignature to extend. not null.
        Returns:
        instance of Future future
        Throws:
        KSIException - when error occurs (e.g when communication with KSI service fails)

      • asyncExtend

        Future<KSISignature> asyncExtend(KSISignature signature,
                                 PublicationRecord publicationRecord)
                          throws KSIException
        This method is used to extend signature asynchronously to the given publication. Use method Future.getResult() to get the extended keyless signature.
        Parameters:
        signature - instance of KSISignature to extend. not null.
        publicationRecord - instance of PublicationRecord to extend the signature.
        Returns:
        instance of Future future
        Throws:
        KSIException - when error occurs (e.g when communication with KSI service fails)

      • getExtendingService

        KSIExtendingService getExtendingService()
        This method is used to get the extender service that the SDK was initialized with. One could use the extender service to get access to its configuration for example.

      • getExtenderConfiguration

        @Deprecated
ExtenderConfiguration getExtenderConfiguration()
                                                    throws KSIException
        Deprecated. Deprecated since 4.10. Use KSIExtendingService.getExtendingConfiguration() in pair with KSIExtendingService.registerExtenderConfigurationListener(ConfigurationListener) instead. One can acquire instance of KSIExtendingService which a KSI instance uses by calling getExtendingService().
        GetExtenderConfiguration method is used to ask extender configuration from KSI gateway/aggregator. Only supported if PduVersion.V2 is used.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - If KSI is initialized with a service not a client.
        KSIException
